<h2>Finish</h2>
			<p>The programme usually takes us up to about 10.00 p.m. in the Palace.
      It may also get a bit chilly and dark by this time, especially in the later weeks
      - we do have lighting, but heating is not feasible.
      </p>
      <p>We usually finish about 10.30 p.m. in Low Port Centre.</p>

<h2>Seating</h2>
<p> There is limited availability of seating at both venues.</p>      

<h2>Wheelchair access</h2>
<p>Palace - one small step</p>
<p>Low Port Centre - ramps and lift.</p>  
<p>At both venues, space is reserved for wheelchairs.</p>        

<h2>Toilets</h2> 
			<p>The Palace has limited accommodation, but has a disabled one.</p>
			<p>There are also toilets in the Burgh Halls in the Kirkgate on the approach to the Palace.</p>
      <p> The Low Port has ample toilets, including some with disabled access.</p>

